"Implement the following plan:\n\n# Plan: Implement Cursor as an External Agent Binary\n\n## Context\n\nThe Cursor agent is currently a built-in agent compiled into the CLI (`cmd/entire/cli/agent/cursor/`). We want to extract it into a standalone external agent binary (`entire-agent-cursor`) that communicates with the CLI via the external agent protocol (subcommand-based JSON over stdin/stdout). This makes Cursor a plugin that can be distributed and updated independently.\n\n## Approach\n\nCreate a self-contained binary at `cmd/entire-agent-cursor/` (single `main` package, no imports from the CLI), then remove the built-in cursor package and its registrations.\n\n## New Files: `cmd/entire-agent-cursor/`\n\nAll files in `package main`. Uses `os.Args[1]` switch + `flag.NewFlagSet` for subcommand dispatch (same pattern as `cmd/entire-agent-test/main.go`).\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `main.go` | Entrypoint, subcommand dispatch switch |\n| `info.go` | `info` (static metadata + capabilities) and `detect` (check `.cursor/` dir) |\n| `session.go` | `get-session-id`, `get-session-dir`, `resolve-session-file`, `read-session`, `write-session`, `format-resume-command` |\n| `transcript.go` | `read-transcript`, `chunk-transcript`, `reassemble-transcript` |\n| `hooks.go` | `parse-hook`, `install-hooks`, `uninstall-hooks`, `are-hooks-installed` |\n| `analyzer.go` | `get-transcript-position`, `extract-modified-files`, `extract-prompts`, `extract-summary` |\n| `types.go` | Cursor hook input structs (sessionStartRaw, stopHookInputRaw, etc.) + event type constants |\n| `helpers.go` | `writeJSON`, `fatal`, `repoRoot()`, `marshalIndentWithNewline`, `stripIDEContextTags`, `chunkJSONL`, `reassembleJSONL`, `readJSON[T]` |\n| `transcript_parse.go` | JSONL transcript parsing (Line, ParseFromBytes, ParseFromFileAtLine, ExtractUserContent) |\n\n### Key Implementation Details\n\n**`info` declares these capabilities:**\n```json\n{\n  \"hooks\": true,\n  \"transcript_analyzer\": true,\n  \"transcript_preparer\": false,\n  \"token_calculator\": false,\n  \"text_generator\": false,\n  \"hook_response_writer\": false,\n  \"subagent_aware_extractor\": false\n}\n```\n\n**Reimplemented dependencies (~200 lines total):**\n- `repoRoot()` -> reads `ENTIRE_REPO_ROOT` env var, falls back to `git rev-parse --show-toplevel`\n- `chunkJSONL`/`reassembleJSONL` -> copy from `cmd/entire/cli/agent/chunking.go:73-118`\n- `stripIDEContextTags` -> copy regex logic from `cmd/entire/cli/textutil/ide_tags.go`\n- Transcript parsing -> copy from `cmd/entire/cli/transcript/parse.go`\n- `marshalIndentWithNewline` -> copy from `cmd/entire/cli/jsonutil/json.go`\n- Logging -> simple `fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, ...)` instead of structured logging\n\n**`parse-hook` event mapping** (from `lifecycle.go`):\n- `session-start` -> type 1 (SessionStart)\n- `before-submit-prompt` -> type 2 (TurnStart), includes prompt/model\n- `stop` -> type 3 (TurnEnd)\n- `pre-compact` -> type 4 (Compaction)\n- `session-end` -> type 5 (SessionEnd)\n- `subagent-start` -> type 6 (SubagentStart), filtered on non-empty Task\n- `subagent-stop` -> type 7 (SubagentEnd), filtered on non-empty Task\n\n**`extract-modified-files`:** Returns `{\"files\": null, \"current_position\": 0}` (Cursor transcripts lack tool_use blocks).\n\n## Files to Remove\n\n- **Delete** `cmd/entire/cli/agent/cursor/` (entire directory - cursor.go, hooks.go, lifecycle.go, transcript.go, types.go, AGENT.md, and all test files)\n\n## Files to Modify\n\n1. **`cmd/entire/cli/hooks_cmd.go`**: Remove `_ \"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent/cursor\"` import. The cursor agent will be discovered via `external.DiscoverAndRegister()` which already runs on line 29.\n\n2. **`cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_condensation_test.go`**: Remove `_ \"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent/cursor\"` import. Tests that call `agent.GetByAgentType(agent.AgentTypeCursor)` (lines 36, 186, 200) need to be updated to skip when cursor isn't registered (it won't be in unit tests since the external binary isn't on PATH):\n   ```go\n   ag, err := agent.GetByAgentType(agent.AgentTypeCursor)\n   if err != nil {\n       t.Skip(\"cursor agent not registered (external binary not on PATH)\")\n   }\n   ```\n\n3. **`cmd/entire/cli/agent/registry.go`**: Keep `AgentNameCursor` and `AgentTypeCursor` constants (used across explain.go, summarize.go, condensation.go, etc.).\n\n## Tests\n\n- Port test logic from `cursor_test.go`, `hooks_test.go`, `lifecycle_test.go`, `transcript_test.go` into new test files in `cmd/entire-agent-cursor/`\n- Test each subcommand handler by invoking main or calling the handler functions directly\n- Test helper functions (chunkJSONL, stripIDEContextTags, transcript parsing, path sanitization)\n\n## Verification\n\n1. `go build ./cmd/entire-agent-cursor/` - binary compiles\n2. `./entire-agent-cursor info` - returns valid JSON with correct capabilities\n3. `mise run fmt && mise run lint` - passes\n4. `mise run test:ci` - all tests pass (condensation tests skip gracefully)\n5. Place binary on PATH, set `external_agents: true` in settings, verify `entire enable` discovers cursor\n\n\nIf you need specific details from before exiting plan mode (like exact code snippets, error messages, or content you generated), read the full transcript at: /Users/nodo/.claude/projects/-Users-nodo-work-cli/31acaad1-8153-4f2b-99b0-52ed107ac58a.jsonl\n\n---\n\nnow I would like to manually test the new setup, can you setup `/Users/nodo/work/test-1` to use 1. the newly build entire cli 2. the new entire-agent-cursor 3. add the feature flag to the repo to use external agents\n\n---\n\ncan you test that for me?\n\n---\n\n[Request interrupted by user]"